\section{Random variables}

\subsection{Setting}

Describe some science, build up problem statement


\subsection{Problem statement}

How to model the world?  
\begin{itemize}
\item Newton said it is all clock work
\item Worked pretty well--called the enlightenment
\item But as did his phyisics, it broke down at the edges
\item Not everything is deterministic
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Visacalc spread sheet view (aka Lotus 123/modern clones)}
\begin{itemize}
\item A ``random'' spread sheet
\item Each row is a possible outcome
\item Definition: A column in a random spreadsheet is called a random variable.
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Programming view}
\begin{itemize}
\item A computer program is deterministic
\item How can it model a random variable? By using a random
subroutine.  
\end{itemize}

\section{Complex combinations of random variables: Ballot problem}

Problem: opening ballots one at a time.

Model: Each is 50/50.



\subsection{Why 50/50 for ballots?}

Problem: what probability to use for the ballot problem?

Model: median voter.  Move to far and you change parties.



